In this article, First Lady Jill Biden speaks at the Indian Treaty Room in the Eisenhower Executive Office Building about the importance of gun violence prevention. She acknowledges the dedicated team working in the Office of Gun Violence Prevention and expresses gratitude for their commitment. Biden shares the stories of young victims of gun violence, highlighting the devastating impact it has on families and communities. She emphasizes the need for action and prevention to protect children from gun violence. Biden also thanks educators for their efforts and discusses the responsibility they have in keeping students safe. She concludes by urging everyone to work together to bring about change and protect children from the tragedy of gun violence. The article ends with a mention of Secretary Miguel Cardona, who is fighting for students and educators.